    {
      "key": {
        "uuid": "417918c1_2def6c0d",
        "filename": "swarming_logger/go/swarming_logger/main.go",
        "patchSetId": 3
      },
      "lineNbr": 51,
      "author": {
        "id": 5120
      },
      "writtenOn": "2017-04-26T17:29:27Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "I\u0027m not sure PubSub will work well for this purpose, for a couple reasons:\n1. This handler will be called every time the task status changes. That means we\u0027ll see the beginning of the output in the logs at least twice, once after the task starts running and once when the task is finished.\n2. PubSub is not exactly guaranteed delivery -- if this handler returns false too many times (e.g. swarming is temporarily down or overloaded) for the same PubSub message, that message gets dropped on the floor. (I suspect that there are other cases where messages get lost also.)\n\nI\u0027m happy with this as v0.5, since I can\u0027t think of a more robust solution that doesn\u0027t require either remembering a lot of things or querying for a lot of things.",
      "range": {
        "startLine": 51,
        "startChar": 22,
        "endLine": 51,
        "endChar": 42
      },
      "revId": "78097d17b389acd434a99749cbe09a9967fe7a50",
      "serverId": "5086850b-e599-37d2-8ec8-ff16aeccbf02",
      "unresolved": true
    },
    {
      "key": {
        "uuid": "cfd54f2b_f2ff1c41",
        "filename": "swarming_logger/go/swarming_logger/main.go",
        "patchSetId": 3
      },
      "lineNbr": 51,
      "author": {
        "id": 5015
      },
      "writtenOn": "2017-04-26T18:21:28Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "Okay, changed to skip unfinished tasks to address #1.  As for #2, I don\u0027t know of a good alternative.  I originally thought about building this whole process into Task Scheduler, which wouldn\u0027t solve the problem per se, but would at least get us aligned.  Personally, I think there\u0027s enough exponential backoff between requests and enough attempts that both this app and Swarming would have to be down for a long time in order to drop messages.  A possible alternative is to use the task scheduler DB, scan through tasks from the last N days and upload any logs we haven\u0027t uploaded yet (not sure how to check that).",
      "parentUuid": "417918c1_2def6c0d",
      "range": {
        "startLine": 51,
        "startChar": 22,
        "endLine": 51,
        "endChar": 42
      },
      "revId": "78097d17b389acd434a99749cbe09a9967fe7a50",
      "serverId": "5086850b-e599-37d2-8ec8-ff16aeccbf02",
      "unresolved": true
    },
    {
      "key": {
        "uuid": "aff42197_83251ac2",
        "filename": "swarming_logger/go/swarming_logger/main.go",
        "patchSetId": 3
      },
      "lineNbr": 51,
      "author": {
        "id": 5120
      },
      "writtenOn": "2017-04-26T20:28:42Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "If it\u0027s important for every task to have logs uploaded, you need belt-and-suspenders for when PubSub doesn\u0027t work. If not, shrug.\n\nAn alternative that could work (in theory):\n - Keep track of (and persist) the earliest-created running task and the completed time of the last task logged.\n - On startup, read all tasks since the earliest-created. If any completed after the last task logged, log them.\n - GetModifiedTasks to notice new running tasks and task completions.\n\nOne reason this might not work in practice is that we might not see the completed tasks in the order they completed.",
      "parentUuid": "cfd54f2b_f2ff1c41",
      "range": {
        "startLine": 51,
        "startChar": 22,
        "endLine": 51,
        "endChar": 42
      },
      "revId": "78097d17b389acd434a99749cbe09a9967fe7a50",
      "serverId": "5086850b-e599-37d2-8ec8-ff16aeccbf02",
      "unresolved": false
    },
    {
      "key": {
        "uuid": "492bc5c8_506c3203",
        "filename": "swarming_logger/go/swarming_logger/main.go",
        "patchSetId": 3
      },
      "lineNbr": 51,
      "author": {
        "id": 5015
      },
      "writtenOn": "2017-04-27T12:41:13Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "So, for the initial use case (manual search) I think it\u0027s okay to occasionally drop a task.  That should be rare, anyway.  In the future, if/when we do more interesting things with the logs, we\u0027ll probably need to re-evaluate.  Each log entry has an insert ID so if we\u0027re smart about it (ie. use task IDs) we\u0027ll be able to determine whether we\u0027ve already logged a task.",
      "parentUuid": "aff42197_83251ac2",
      "range": {
        "startLine": 51,
        "startChar": 22,
        "endLine": 51,
        "endChar": 42
      },
      "revId": "78097d17b389acd434a99749cbe09a9967fe7a50",
      "serverId": "5086850b-e599-37d2-8ec8-ff16aeccbf02",
      "unresolved": false
    },
